<TITLE> 3 children injured in Lalbagh blast </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 10 (bdnews24.com)  Three children were injured in a blast at a field adjacent to Shahidnagar slum near Lalbagh Fort in old Dhaka on Wednesday. The blast took place at around 12:15 pm, said deputy commissioner (Lalbagh) of Dhaka Metropolitan Police, Anwar Hossain. The injured are, Shafiqul, 1, Jhumur, 6, and Akhi, 8. They were admitted to the Dhaka Medical College. They were playing in the field with a bottle, which apparently was a home-made bomb. At one point it blew up, said Hossain, adding "it could have been left by some criminals". bdne
